attributes.Long form description: The student starts the task by aligning and screwing each of the four legs to the middle shelf, once they are all screwed the student proceeds to attach the table top in between the four legs and then securing it using the hex socket heads, and finally he makes sure all the hex socket heads are tight enough to complete his task.

attributes.Transcription: So please assemble this small table.

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the first leg on the shelf.

attributes.Transcription: You should start by taking one of the plates and putting them on the table with the longest side on the table, so up but with the longest side.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Student should put the tray up.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Student should put the longer side on the table.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Student should put the longer side on the table.

attributes.Transcription: All right, and now you can fix one of the legs on this plate. This plate is going to be on the middle shelf. So it should be aligned with the middles.

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the second leg of the shelf.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Student should rotate the shelf first.

attributes.Transcription: Please rotate the shelf that the leg is laying on the table. It'll be more stable.

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the third leg on the shelf.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Student should first assemble all four legs.

attributes.Transcription: Oh, start by putting the four legs on.

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the fourth leg of the shelf.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Student should  keep the shelf laying down on the table.

attributes.Transcription: Please keep the shelf laying down on the table to place the top shelf.

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the table top.
The student assembles the other side of the top shelf.

attributes.Transcription: The last step is to put the shelf standing up and secure all the screws.

attributes.Action sentence: The student screws the table screws.

attributes.Transcription: You can press the stop button.
